review_text:
The Banque Centrale Populaire is a Moroccan bank, founded in 1961,[1] and has played a major role in the Moroccan economy. The bank describes itself as having the largest branch network in Morocco.[2] It provides services to more than 3.2 million customers, and the bank acquires 60% of the total local savings of the Moroccan diaspora abroad. It is the first internationally recognized bank in Morocco. The bank has offices in Germany, England, Canada, Spain, France, Gibraltar, the Netherlands, Belgium and Italy.[3]
In 2011, it ranked fortieth in the Forbes Middle East list of the 100 most powerful companies in the Arab world.[4]

review_text: Is there any phone number to contact with !

I would like to express my great disappointment with the customer service of the Banque du Maroc.
Having tried to change my phone number via the mobile application, my request was refused, forcing me to physically go to an agency. Living abroad, this involves taking a plane ticket, which is totally unacceptable for such a simple procedure.

Additionally, when I asked to speak to a manager to understand the situation, I was hung up on several times, and my attempts to call back went unanswered. This lack of consideration and efficiency is inexcusable and does not reflect the service that a customer has the right to expect.

I strongly advise against this bank, whose staff would rather hang up than resolve a problem. Although the application fee is always collected without fail, it is impossible to get help when you need it. This lack of professionalism is unacceptable.

review_text:
I am a customer over 50 years old of the Banque Populaire d’Oujda. In December 2020 I went to Istanbul for medical treatment, the cash I took to cover medical expenses, I wanted to use my bank card with a tourist amount, all the ATMs refused the transaction.
By calling the head of the Al Wilaya d'Oujda agency (out of more than 40 calls) I was answered twice without any solution...
I sent a complaint to the CEO of the Banque Populaire d'Oujda on 01/06/2021, after 40 days of waiting, I was called to see the director (Ms. Belahcen) at 3:30 p.m. she left me waiting until 4:15 p.m. when I left. I call that negligence towards customers. This kind of behavior neither works in the interests of the bank nor the trust of its customers..
Leaving a customer hanging around in a foreign country with his money who cannot use it puts us in total distrust of this bank..
Conclusion * “master carte Gold” bank card which I consider unreliable,
* poor service from the head of the agency indicated above,
* Negligence of complaints to the CEO of BP Oujda (01/06/2021 and 02/15/2021)

review_text:
Not worth a star!
No decent service, I tried to withdraw money from the bank machine, the money is withdrawn immediately, but I can't get anything in my hands?! It looked like I wasn't the only one when I walked into the office to talk to the bank employee about it.
She referred to the cash machine that they were replenishing hence the incident at the cash machine. How can one have bank transactions carried out when they are replenishing the cash machine? This wouldn't be possible, what do we expect?
She assured me that the money will be back in the account in 30 minutes max to 2 hours.
It's now been a month and I haven't gotten my money back yet? Where things go wrong, God knows, but this is not service!
I have learned my lesson not to use my bank card outside Europe anymore!
Please transfer my money to the bank itself quickly or I will have to come to the office, which will not be a pleasant visit!

review_text: horrible service careful using sht bank especially agency manager really unprofessional impolite short worst bank ever seen stay away

Personally, I think that there are many points to improve, notably awareness of the role of the banker and a sense of service as well as customer relationship management to improve the customer experience. I believe this is the basis in this sector of activity.

Unfortunately, during your visit you will notice that the staff of this agency always seem overwhelmed by back office tasks. So, at a simple different request, he sends you back to come back another day as if it's an unpleasant and additional task for him that he didn't plan to do.

And the worst thing is that if you want to get the information by phone it's impossible. No one answers telephone calls to the agency's landline at any time of the day and to all its numbers.

A back and forth which is unpleasant and which wastes time for everyone but above all the relationship of trust which is supposed to be established with the banker.

To the wise...

I thought it was a modern bank with real added value in the customer journey, particularly thanks to the digital advances of their platform. Unfortunately, from a customer relations point of view we could hardly do worse, especially for customers who do not live in Morocco. Contacting the agency is a real ordeal: the phone never picks up, the advisors leave their cell phones with you but very rarely respond (with endless delays). When your advisor is on vacation or overwhelmed, he or she refers you to the agency director. This promises to process your requests then blocks your number... Cutting short any hope of communication.
Only small mishaps that say a lot about the level of respect for customers and the values ​​of the bank (of the agency at least). For me, this will be enough to explore the market and change banks.

review_text:
**Avoid this bank branch at all costs!**

I am extremely disappointed with the services of this bank agency. Firstly, it is practically impossible to reach them by phone. I have tried to call them several times, but they never answer. It’s frustrating and a huge lack of respect for their customers.

Additionally, the agency is constantly crowded. No matter what time you show up, expect to spend hours in a never-ending queue. Their organization is chaotic and the staff seems completely overwhelmed.

To top it all off, they regularly close before the official closing time. This has happened to me several times, where I wasted time traveling only to find the agency closed well before the indicated time. This is unacceptable for a bank supposed to be at the service of its customers.

In summary, this agency is seriously lacking in professionalism and respect for its clients. I strongly advise against setting foot there if you want to avoid frustration and unnecessary waste of time.

review_text:
Depuis toujours, le service de cette agence est catastrophique. Le personnel n’a jamais su se professionnaliser, et l’accueil est loin d’être digne d’une banque. La caissière 3 (encore jeune) agit comme si nous étions chez elle, et la caissière 1 offre un service lamentable : elle a laissé un client en plein traitement pour en servir un autre qu’elle connaissait personnellement, en passant sur une autre caisse, sans même demander l’autorisation.
Concernant mon cas, ma grand-mère a demandé les trois derniers relevés bancaires, mais on ne lui en a donné que deux, alors qu’elle ne peut pas se déplacer plusieurs fois à la banque. Le lendemain, je suis allée avec elle pour récupérer le troisième relevé, et l’employée m’a répondu d’une manière irrespectueuse en prétendant qu’elle avait déjà remis tous les documents. Pourtant, les trois derniers relevés concernent bien les mois de décembre, janvier et février !
Un service totalement incompétent et un manque de professionnalisme flagrant. Je déconseille fortement cette agence !

Disappointing customer experience in this Elwifaq agency in Agadir.
- The waiting list system does not work, which leads to frustration and long waits.

- The file that I had prepared and sent online for the creation of my account never arrived at the agency, thus causing an unnecessary delay and a waste of time for everyone.

- The agency appeared to be facing major IT problems. The printer was not working, preventing necessary documents from being printed, and the remittance system was out of service, making any financial transaction impossible. These technical malfunctions not only prolonged the process but also created an atmosphere of chaos and incompetence.

- Another point to note: the lack of chairs, not only did I have to stand while creating my account, but this was also the case for a large part of the customers present. This made the wait even more painful.

However, I would like to point out that Mrs Bizgarn, the advisor, was really helpful and attentive despite these difficult conditions. She did her best to help.

I hope that this feedback will be taken into account to improve the waiting conditions and services of this agency.
